title: Air raid sirens wail across Ukraine in first moments of 2023 as fresh blasts heard in Kyiv
description: Blasts have been heard in Kyiv and air raid sirens wailed across the country just after midnight, forcing Ukrainians to abandon New Year celebrations and head to bomb shelters.

title: World politics and power - the dates and trends that will help shape 2023 | Adam Boulton
description: The major events which come define a year, or even a decade, are seldom predicted.

title: At least 15 killed including four children in Mexico bus crash
description: At least 15 people have died after a bus crashed in Mexico, including four children, local officials have said.

title: World leaders and King Charles pay tribute to former pope nicknamed 'God's Rottweiler'
description: World leaders and King Charles have paid tribute to former pope Benedict XVI following his death at the age of 95.

title: Explosions in Kyiv as Ukrainians warned of missiles across country
description: People across Ukraine have been urged to take cover as air raid sirens sound and explosions have been reported in the capital.

title: Former Pope Benedict XVI, the first to resign in centuries, dies aged 95
description: Former pope Benedict XVI, who became the first pontiff to resign in some 600 years, has died aged 95.

title: Barbados may hit Cumberbatch family with reparation claim over historic links to slave trade
description: The family of Oscar-nominated actor Benedict Cumberbatch is reportedly facing the prospect of legal action over its historic links to the slave trade in Barbados.

title: A welcome pitch invasion - Spanish football fans shower field with toys for kids
description: Fans of Spanish La Liga club Real Betis have kept up with their annual gift-giving tradition and showered their pitch with 14,000 toys for disadvantaged children.
